CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 19, 1961, pg. 15, reads: "Smiling Young Ladies - Shown above are a group of young beauties at the recent Beta Phi Alpha and Alpha Phi Beta dance at Loendi Club. They are, front row, left to right: Veronica (Cookie) Gloster, Judy Nelson, Eloise Drake, Dolly Mellix, Elaine Drake, president of Beta Phi Alpha; Mrs. Keith, the sponsor; Pat Calloway, Sandra Holmes, Mary Alice Calloway, and back row, left to right: Karen Kemp, Iris Keys, and Carmen Leftwich. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of women, including Veronica "Cookie" Gloster, Judy Nelson, Eloise Drake, Dolly Mellix, Elaine Drake, Mrs. Keith, Pat Calloway, Sandra Holmes, Mary Alice Calloway; back row: Karen Kemp, Iris Keys, and Carmen Leftwich, posed in Loendi Club for Beta Phi Alpha and Alpha Phi Beta dance
